.SH RETURN VALUE
.PD
.TP
\f[B]0\f[R]
Success.
.PD
.TP
\f[B]1\f[R]
Generic error code for: missing command\-line argument, too many
command\-line arguments, unknown option, mount point is not empty, etc.
.PD
.TP
\f[B]10\f[R]
Cannot create the mount point.
.PD
.TP
\f[B]11\f[R]
Cannot open the archive file.
.PD
.TP
\f[B]12\f[R]
Cannot create the cache file.
.PD
.TP
\f[B]13\f[R]
Cannot write to the cache file.
This is most likely an indication that there is not enough temporary
space.
.PD
.TP
\f[B]20\f[R]
The archive contains an encrypted file, but no password was provided.
.PD
.TP
\f[B]21\f[R]
The archive contains an encrypted file, and the provided password does
not decrypt it.
.PD
.TP
\f[B]22\f[R]
The archive contains an encrypted file, and the encryption method is not
supported.
.PD
.TP
\f[B]30\f[R]
Cannot recognize the archive format.
.PD
.TP
\f[B]31\f[R]
Invalid archive header.
.PD
.TP
\f[B]32\f[R]
Cannot read and extract the archive.
